26
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:29,916
♪♪

27
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,125
[ Playing
"Piano Sonata Number 8" ]

28
00:02:32,208 --> 00:02:40,458
♪♪

29
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:41,125
Done, Ms. Seto.

30
00:02:41,208 --> 00:02:43,125
Well, Teach, have at it.

31
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,083
I'm ready
for your feedback, sir.

32
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:50,208
No pulling any punches.

33
00:02:50,291 --> 00:02:52,333
Hmph!

34
00:02:52,416 --> 00:02:55,041
The pianissimo part sounded like
you were marching off to war,

35
00:02:55,125 --> 00:02:57,583
and your rests
were just sloppy.

36
00:02:57,666 --> 00:02:59,458
You wrinkled your brow
from start to finish,

37
00:02:59,541 --> 00:03:00,833
and your posture's abysmal,

38
00:03:00,916 --> 00:03:02,375
and quit gritting your teeth
like you're in pain.

39
00:03:02,458 --> 00:03:06,208
Your left hand lags a bit
on the rhythm, too.

40
00:03:06,291 --> 00:03:07,500
My hands are small,

41
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:09,375
so my fingers
can't reach as far across.

42
00:03:09,458 --> 00:03:11,833
Move your wrists a bit,
and you'll be fine.

43
00:03:11,916 --> 00:03:13,666
Play the first beat
with your little finger,

44
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:16,791
and then use that momentum to
take your wrist over like this.

45
00:03:16,875 --> 00:03:19,583
Then just move it
to where you can play the note.

46
00:03:23,958 --> 00:03:25,833
How about changing up
your pedal work?

47
00:03:25,916 --> 00:03:27,541
Might do the trick,
right?

48
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:30,583
That isn't going
to help me win.

49
00:03:30,666 --> 00:03:33,750
Honoring the score
is all that matters!

50
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:35,208
The score
is perfection,

51
00:03:35,291 --> 00:03:36,875
and we are lowly servants
of that perfection!

52
00:03:36,958 --> 00:03:37,875
Well, that was abrupt.

53
00:03:37,958 --> 00:03:39,666
You can say that again.

54
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:42,916
Playing a song any other way
than how it's written down

55
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,375
is just the refuge
of a lesser musician.

56
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:46,875
[ Sighs ]

57
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:48,625
Kaori:
Just play with sincerity.

58
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:49,875
Give the performance
of your life

59
00:03:49,958 --> 00:03:51,083
with everything you've got.

60
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:54,708
The score's not
some perfect thing.

61
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:55,708
It's there to interpret,

62
00:03:55,791 --> 00:03:58,333
an emotional roadmap

63
00:03:58,416 --> 00:04:00,875
left by those
who have come before us.

64
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:02,458
<i>And I...</i>

65
00:04:02,541 --> 00:04:04,875
<i>I'm just now learning</i>
<i>how to read them.</i>

66
00:04:04,958 --> 00:04:06,541
[ Gasps ] What a cliché.

67
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:07,708
[ Shrieks ]

68
00:04:07,791 --> 00:04:10,458
<i>Spouting sentimental drivel</i>
<i>like that.</i>

69
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:12,750
<i>No wonder you burned out</i>
<i>by my age.</i>

70
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:16,583
[ Indistinct conversations ]

71
00:04:16,666 --> 00:04:21,375
♪♪

72
00:04:21,458 --> 00:04:23,500
Kousei:<i> I have a bit of time</i>
<i>before the lesson.</i>

73
00:04:23,583 --> 00:04:25,166
Kaori: I realized
I hadn't heard

74
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:26,625
your dumb voice
for a while.

75
00:04:26,708 --> 00:04:32,750
♪♪

76
00:04:32,833 --> 00:04:35,166
<i>Oh, that's right.</i>

77
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:38,666
<i>I should get her some sweets.</i>

78
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:43,041
<i>Like those canelés you wanted.</i>

79
00:04:46,125 --> 00:04:48,375
<i>You always pop up</i>
<i>out of nowhere.</i>

80
00:04:48,458 --> 00:04:51,666
<i>I'm not ready,</i>
<i>but here you are.</i>

81
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:54,500
Hey, it's you.

82
00:04:56,541 --> 00:04:57,041
Who are you again?

83
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:58,916
Wait! Amnesia?!

84
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,208
Is it 'cause
she hit her head?!

85
00:05:00,291 --> 00:05:01,541
[ Distorted ]
Sorry to forget you,

86
00:05:01,625 --> 00:05:03,416
but I haven't
seen your face lately.

87
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,916
If only
you'd come to visit,

88
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,458
maybe we could have
avoided this.

89
00:05:06,541 --> 00:05:07,958
Actually,
I was on my --

90
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:09,916
You didn't happen
to see Watari, did you?

91
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,333
I'm here to surprise him
when he passes by.

92
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:15,708
Watari? Uh...

93
00:05:15,791 --> 00:05:17,666
he's still at school,
I think.

94
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,791
I'll go check.

95
00:05:19,875 --> 00:05:21,375
[ Gasps ]

96
00:05:21,458 --> 00:05:24,291
Never let it be said
that I am not merciful.

97
00:05:24,375 --> 00:05:26,333
Even though you abandoned me
to my fate,

98
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:28,791
I'm gonna give you
a shot to make things right.

99
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:30,416
I'll let you be
Watari's stand-in again.

100
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:32,708
Hmph!

101
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:36,541
It worked out before.
[ Grunts ]

102
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:39,250
[ Distorted ] And I bet
you can carry a lot.

103
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:41,666
[ Shoppers squealing ]

104
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:43,958
Kaori:
These prices are amazing!

105
00:05:44,041 --> 00:05:46,333
Take your grubby mitts
off of that!

106
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:49,208
You're making those sundresses
all wrinkled! I'll destroy you!

107
00:05:49,291 --> 00:05:50,291
[ Shrieks ]
I, uh...

108
00:05:50,375 --> 00:05:52,375
I got a lesson to --

109
00:05:52,458 --> 00:05:55,791
[ Gasps ] This tie-wearing
rabbit is adorable!

110
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:57,291
Look at
this cute stationery!

111
00:05:57,375 --> 00:05:57,916
No!
Just send an e-mail!

112
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,333
Come to me, lost kid!

113
00:06:00,416 --> 00:06:02,166
Not a problem!
Not a problem!

114
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:04,291
Woman on PA: Lost child
at the front counter.

115
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:08,833
Woman: There you are!

116
00:06:08,916 --> 00:06:10,333
[ Gasps ]

117
00:06:10,416 --> 00:06:12,000
Mommy!

118
00:06:12,083 --> 00:06:14,500
Oh, you scared me.
[ Sighs ]

119
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:16,875
[ Laughs ]

120
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:18,916
There's nothing
I enjoy in life more

121
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,833
than lending a helping hand.
Hmph.

122
00:06:21,916 --> 00:06:23,708
So grab some of this.

123
00:06:23,791 --> 00:06:26,666
The girl's mom,
she was crying.

124
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:30,250
Yeah. I bet she's been
worried sick about her.

125
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:32,125
No kidding.

126
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:34,875
But I guess we all put our folks
through the wringer somehow.

127
00:06:34,958 --> 00:06:36,583
Hey, did you see?

128
00:06:36,666 --> 00:06:39,208
When I held her hand,
she squeezed it really tightly.

129
00:06:39,291 --> 00:06:41,250
What a cutie.

130
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,458
It's like she was telling me
not to let her go.

131
00:06:43,541 --> 00:06:47,125
Maybe she thought she'd be
all alone in the world

132
00:06:47,208 --> 00:06:49,666
if I let go of her.

133
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:51,166
Uh...

134
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:52,958
Oh, hold on.

135
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:54,583
Are you thirsty?

136
00:06:54,666 --> 00:06:56,041
Oh, yeah.

137
00:06:56,125 --> 00:06:58,541
I meant
to take it back before.

138
00:06:58,625 --> 00:06:59,125
[ Both stammer ]

139
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:01,791
Let me get that.

140
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:05,041
<i>Uniform skirt?</i>

141
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:06,750
<i>So you came to school today.</i>

142
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:09,916
<i>She must be feeling better.</i>

143
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,416
<i>See? She's fine.</i>

144
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:14,083
Wait a sec.
Where's your school bag?

145
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:15,083
[ Gasps ]

146
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:17,875
Uh,
let's go find it.

147
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:19,291
[ Loud piano chord bangs ]

148
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:20,875
He's late!

149
00:07:20,958 --> 00:07:22,875
Stop hitting the keys.

150
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:23,958
Kousei
ain't gonna show up.

151
00:07:24,041 --> 00:07:25,083
What?!

152
00:07:25,166 --> 00:07:25,791
Yeah. He texted me.

153
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:28,083
You tell me this now?!

154
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:30,541
And you're okay with this,
Ms. Seto?

155
00:07:30,625 --> 00:07:32,166
He's being
irresponsible.

156
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:33,958
He'll get his.

157
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:36,708
I want to know why you're always
so eager to sell him out.

158
00:07:36,791 --> 00:07:38,250
Huh? No!

159
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:39,833
I wasn't
selling him out.

160
00:07:39,916 --> 00:07:43,166
I just appreciate
our time here so much.

161
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,958
Look, kid, I don't know
what game you're running...

162
00:07:45,041 --> 00:07:45,958
[ Gasps ]

163
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:47,875
...but if you ever
do anything

164
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:49,250
to try
and dick over Kousei,

165
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:50,583
they're not gonna
find your body.

166
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:54,375
Well...

167
00:07:54,458 --> 00:07:57,125
I guess you must care
for Kousei quite a lot, huh?

168
00:07:57,208 --> 00:07:58,958
I'm kind of
his backup mom.

169
00:07:59,041 --> 00:08:00,666
How come...

170
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:04,291
How come you're even
bothering with me as a
student?

171
00:08:05,875 --> 00:08:08,875
Because I thought it might
give something to Kousei.

172
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:12,750
<i>Something more</i>
<i>than all his sorrow.</i>

173
00:08:13,708 --> 00:08:16,625
Are you sure
you can trust the enemy?

174
00:08:16,708 --> 00:08:19,250
Enemy? Is that
what you are to him?

175
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:21,833
I see two musicians
who are walking the same path.

176
00:08:21,916 --> 00:08:24,375
[ Sighs ]

177
00:08:24,458 --> 00:08:26,208
[ Koharu laughs ]

178
00:08:26,291 --> 00:08:27,666
[ Paper flutters ]

179
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:29,625
Hiroko: Oh, wow!
That's beautiful, baby!

180
00:08:29,708 --> 00:08:31,791
Good job.
Go show Nagi.

181
00:08:31,875 --> 00:08:34,000
Okay. [ Giggles ]

182
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:35,000
Lookit!

183
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:36,000
[ Gasps ]

184
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:37,875
[ Giggles ]

185
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:44,375
♪♪

186
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:47,625
<i>That boy's had</i>
<i>his fill of tears.</i>

187
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:50,958
<i>Let him smile,</i>

188
00:08:51,041 --> 00:08:53,125
<i>in life and music alike.</i>

189
00:08:56,875 --> 00:08:57,833
Kaori: Wow.

190
00:08:57,916 --> 00:08:59,166
It's so dark.

191
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:00,541
Pretty creepy, huh?

192
00:09:00,625 --> 00:09:02,125
Kousei:
Well, it'd be creepier

193
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,041
if this weren't
such a pain in the butt.

194
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:04,875
[ Laughs ]

195
00:09:04,958 --> 00:09:10,916
♪♪

196
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,875
[ Footsteps echoing ]

197
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:17,458
[ Door opens ]

198
00:09:28,958 --> 00:09:30,208
So where's your bag?

199
00:09:30,291 --> 00:09:32,500
[ Gasps ] I wonder.

200
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:33,375
It's got to be
around here somewhere.

201
00:09:33,458 --> 00:09:34,916
It couldn't just
walk away.

202
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,041
[ Wails ]

203
00:09:37,125 --> 00:09:38,541
[ Growls ]

204
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:40,833
You're lying about
the stupid bag, huh?!

205
00:09:40,916 --> 00:09:42,625
It isn't here, okay?

206
00:09:42,708 --> 00:09:44,250
I'm sorry.
Don't be mad.

207
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,958
<i>Wait a second.</i>

208
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:49,833
<i>You didn't have it</i>
<i>this afternoon, either.</i>

209
00:09:49,916 --> 00:09:51,833
Did you
come to school today?

210
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:53,375
The doctors told me

211
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:54,875
I could have a free day
out of the hospital.

212
00:09:54,958 --> 00:09:59,250
I'm sorry. I just wanted
to come here, no matter what.

213
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:02,583
'Cause I was starting
to forget it.

214
00:10:02,666 --> 00:10:04,583
I'm the one
who should apologize.

215
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:07,250
This was your one day out,
and I took it up.

216
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,791
It should have been
Watari here, not me.

217
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:13,791
Are you
going to forget?

218
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:15,000
Huh?

219
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:19,416
The girl who brought you here
on a wild-goose chase,

220
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:22,166
the one you helped when
she found a lost little kid,

221
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:25,791
who snuck out of the hospital
and waited for a boy...

222
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:28,208
are you going to
forget her?

223
00:10:28,291 --> 00:10:32,250
<i>Part of me will echo</i>
<i>in their hearts forever.</i>

224
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:34,250
<i>In some tiny way,</i>

225
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:36,458
<i>these people aren't ever</i>
<i>going to forget about us.</i>

226
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:39,583
<i>I'll never forget</i>
<i>about us.</i>

227
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:43,291
I'll never forget,

228
00:10:43,375 --> 00:10:45,750
no matter what happens.

229
00:10:48,416 --> 00:10:49,291
[ Grunts ]

230
00:10:49,375 --> 00:10:51,958
I'm glad it was you,
you know?

231
00:10:52,041 --> 00:10:53,625
[ Gasps ]
-Are you all right?

232
00:10:53,708 --> 00:10:56,208
Yeah. A little tired.
That's all.

233
00:10:57,916 --> 00:11:01,583
Kaori: Look at you riding double
on a school bike.

234
00:11:01,666 --> 00:11:03,958
Kousei: Hey, it's not like
they're using it.

235
00:11:04,041 --> 00:11:05,791
Sorry about
your lesson.

236
00:11:05,875 --> 00:11:07,083
No big deal.

237
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,416
It's Hiroko,
so it'll all pan out.

238
00:11:10,958 --> 00:11:13,333
For what it's worth,
I'm glad you skipped it.

239
00:11:13,416 --> 00:11:16,166
I had such a wonderful time
with you this afternoon,

240
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,000
best I've had in a while,

241
00:11:18,083 --> 00:11:20,583
so thank you.

242
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:24,250
First
we tackled the mall,

243
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:26,750
then crept through
the school at night.

244
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:30,041
Now you're taking me home
on the back of a bicycle.

245
00:11:30,125 --> 00:11:33,625
Look at them twinkling up there
with all their heart.

246
00:11:35,041 --> 00:11:36,750
<i>Maybe it's the night air,</i>

247
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:39,583
<i>but your words</i>
<i>feel so warm,</i>

248
00:11:39,666 --> 00:11:40,875
<i>like you're whispering them</i>
<i>in my ear.</i>

249
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:46,166
<i>I'll stand in for Watari</i>
<i>anytime gladly...</i>

250
00:11:47,041 --> 00:11:48,250
<i>forever.</i>

251
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:55,083
♪♪

252
00:11:55,166 --> 00:12:02,041
♪♪

253
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:04,833
<i>She wept,</i>
<i>but I wasn't brave enough...</i>

254
00:12:06,958 --> 00:12:08,250
<i>to ask why.</i>

255
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:11,958
It's lagging.
You fall behind,

256
00:12:12,041 --> 00:12:13,208
because you
break it up in your head.

257
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:15,250
<i>No duh. But I'm</i>
<i>playing as fast as possible.</i>

258
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:17,500
<i>I can't go any faster.</i>

259
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:19,166
<i>If you're so great,</i>
<i>you do it.</i>

260
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:21,250
Alright,
watch how I play.

261
00:12:21,958 --> 00:12:23,041
[ Wails ]
There.

262
00:12:23,125 --> 00:12:25,166
Dumb piano!

263
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:26,708
You're such a traitor!
[ Gasps ]

264
00:12:26,791 --> 00:12:28,875
And you,
no fair showing off!

265
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:30,416
[ Chuckles ]
Mnh-mnh.

266
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:33,250
[ Gasps ]
You okay?

267
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:34,500
Uh, yes, sir!

268
00:12:36,291 --> 00:12:37,458
<i>I hate getting it wrong.</i>

269
00:12:37,541 --> 00:12:40,125
Great.
Let's run it one more time.

270
00:12:40,208 --> 00:12:42,791
<i>But what I really hate</i>
<i>is Kousei Arima.</i>

271
00:12:50,416 --> 00:12:53,625
Satsuki: Nagi, did you really
reject that upperclassman?

272
00:12:53,708 --> 00:12:55,541
Komugi: How many
does that make now?

273
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:58,166
Nagi: He was a total bookworm,
not my type.

274
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,750
Any idea what you're
gonna do for the festival yet?

275
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:02,416
Not a clue.

276
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,500
The festival's
in November, Nagi.

277
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:06,500
We need to figure it out
while there's still time.

278
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:08,541
We're allowed to have guests
from outside the school,

279
00:13:08,625 --> 00:13:10,333
right, like graduates?

280
00:13:10,416 --> 00:13:13,583
They say Miike's
bringing in someone famous.

281
00:13:13,666 --> 00:13:15,666
I have other stuff
on my mind right now.

282
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:17,458
<i>Like revenge</i>

283
00:13:17,541 --> 00:13:20,791
<i>and how I'm gonna get mine</i>
<i>against that stupid Arima.</i>

284
00:13:20,875 --> 00:13:22,791
[ Chuckles ]
What's she laughing about?!

285
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:24,208
Just leave it alone.

286
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:27,000
You know, our school
does have a reputation

287
00:13:27,083 --> 00:13:28,458
for its top students
putting on

288
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:31,791
pretty spectacular performances
for this show.

289
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:35,125
And if you're not one of them,
I don't know who is.

290
00:13:35,208 --> 00:13:36,500
<i>Me, one of our best?</i>

291
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:40,416
<i>She's right. I'm the Angel</i>
<i>of Kurumi Junior High,</i>

292
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:41,875
<i>perfection itself!</i>

293
00:13:41,958 --> 00:13:43,791
Both: Ahh! She's a monster!

294
00:13:43,875 --> 00:13:45,625
Nagi:<i> So why does he ding me</i>
<i>for every little mistake!</i>

295
00:13:45,708 --> 00:13:48,458
Slow down.
Your fingers slip

296
00:13:48,541 --> 00:13:50,125
because
you play it too fast.

297
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:52,041
Forte and allegro
aren't the same thing.

298
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:54,916
[ Wails ]

299
00:13:55,041 --> 00:13:57,833
Nagi, wait!
Where are you going?!

300
00:13:57,916 --> 00:13:58,625
Hiroko: Go get her, Teach.
Huh?

301
00:13:58,708 --> 00:14:00,208
Comes with the territory.

302
00:14:00,291 --> 00:14:01,458
Trust me.

303
00:14:01,541 --> 00:14:04,166
[ Bird squawking ]

304
00:14:05,625 --> 00:14:08,458
<i>What am I supposed to do?</i>

305
00:14:08,541 --> 00:14:10,333
<i>My stupid hands are too small.</i>

306
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:12,333
[ Running footsteps ]

307
00:14:12,416 --> 00:14:14,375
[ Kousei panting ]

308
00:14:25,083 --> 00:14:26,333
Hiroko thought
you might be here. [ Chuckles ]

309
00:14:26,416 --> 00:14:28,500
Hmph!
[ Sputters ]

310
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:33,458
Hey, I'm sorry.

311
00:14:33,541 --> 00:14:37,208
I'm kind of figuring out
this teaching thing as I go.

312
00:14:37,291 --> 00:14:37,750
You want a snack?

313
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:39,166
Here.
Hmm.

314
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:42,833
You're bribing me
with a sweet potato?!

315
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:44,875
Just look at it,
all warm and delicious.

316
00:14:44,958 --> 00:14:46,875
I bet you
it'll melt in your mouth.

317
00:14:46,958 --> 00:14:47,875
[ Groans ]

318
00:14:47,958 --> 00:14:49,375
[ Sighs ]

319
00:14:49,458 --> 00:14:52,250
[ Squeals ]

320
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:55,083
Mmm!

321
00:14:55,166 --> 00:14:57,541
Agh!

322
00:14:57,625 --> 00:14:59,916
<i>He totally bought me off</i>
<i>with a snack!</i>

323
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,375
It's very pretty
out here.

324
00:15:01,458 --> 00:15:03,041
Yeah, huh?

325
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:05,375
I used to play
on these steps a lot

326
00:15:05,458 --> 00:15:07,750
with my favorite person
in the world.

327
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:09,125
Boy:<i> Come on, Nagi!</i>

328
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:10,416
<i>You got to keep up, okay?!</i>

329
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,166
<i>Wait for me!</i>

330
00:15:14,125 --> 00:15:18,083
Nagi: The truth is he got into
playing the piano first,

331
00:15:18,166 --> 00:15:22,208
so I've kind of been following
in his footsteps.

332
00:15:22,291 --> 00:15:23,958
Kousei: You admire him.

333
00:15:24,041 --> 00:15:27,916
Yeah, but he spends all
his time pursuing his big
rival,

334
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:32,375
and now it feels like
he's just kind of stuck,

335
00:15:32,458 --> 00:15:34,916
like he doesn't even realize
how good he is.

336
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:40,291
It's the reason I play piano,
because he inspired me.

337
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:41,583
I want him to know that.

338
00:15:41,666 --> 00:15:45,541
<i>Why am I admitting</i>
<i>all of this to Arima?</i>

339
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,125
<i>He's a jerk-face.</i>

340
00:15:47,208 --> 00:15:49,083
[<i> Scoffs</i> ]
<i>What about my vengeance?</i>

341
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:52,500
Huh?

342
00:15:52,583 --> 00:15:53,916
I guess I play
for the wrong reason.

343
00:15:56,291 --> 00:15:57,416
For what it's worth,

344
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,833
you wouldn't be
the first.

345
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:03,208
<i>Maybe I wanted you to tell me</i>
<i>it's okay to play for him,</i>

346
00:16:03,291 --> 00:16:05,875
<i>that I don't have to</i>
<i>feel bad about it.</i>

347
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,416
Both: 1, 2, 3!

348
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:12,333
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6.

349
00:16:12,416 --> 00:16:15,000
Let's go again!

350
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:17,458
1, 2, 3!

351
00:16:17,541 --> 00:16:20,416
Now you got to tell me if
there's someone you like a lot.

352
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:22,000
Not really.
Uh-huh!

353
00:16:22,083 --> 00:16:24,125
It's written
all over your face.

354
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:24,750
What kind of girl is she?

355
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:26,458
You want to know, huh?

356
00:16:26,541 --> 00:16:29,000
Okay, I'll tell you.

357
00:16:29,083 --> 00:16:32,083
She's the kind of girl
who already likes my friend.

358
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:34,791
I see.

359
00:16:34,875 --> 00:16:37,458
And that's a good enough reason
to just give up?

360
00:16:37,541 --> 00:16:38,458
[ Gasps ]

361
00:16:38,541 --> 00:16:40,583
1, 2, 3.

362
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:43,500
It's pretty cliché,
you know,

363
00:16:43,583 --> 00:16:45,666
friends over love.

364
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:49,250
Yeah,
you're not wrong,

365
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:52,833
but sometimes life makes
the decision for you.

366
00:16:52,916 --> 00:16:54,708
Hmm.

367
00:16:54,791 --> 00:16:57,291
1, 2, 3, 4...

368
00:16:57,375 --> 00:16:58,625
Tell me
something about her.

369
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:01,125
She makes me feel

370
00:17:01,208 --> 00:17:04,125
like I'm strapped in
to a roller coaster.

371
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:06,416
It's hard
to catch my breath.

372
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,875
I'm laughing and crying
all at once.

373
00:17:07,958 --> 00:17:11,208
Just by being around...
[ Bow clatters ]

374
00:17:11,291 --> 00:17:14,500
...she's taken my monochrome
world and filled it with
color.

375
00:17:14,583 --> 00:17:15,791
She's like a firework.

376
00:17:15,875 --> 00:17:19,500
throwing radiance
into the night.

377
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:24,541
Oh, hi,
Mr. Brought No Canelés!

378
00:17:24,625 --> 00:17:26,541
You had one job,
Friend A, one job!

379
00:17:26,625 --> 00:17:28,750
What the heck
is wrong with you?!

380
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,750
Watari's got
all the sugar you need.

381
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:32,291
The day has been saved.

382
00:17:32,375 --> 00:17:34,500
I know why he forgot
to bring 'em today.

383
00:17:34,583 --> 00:17:35,541
Word on the street
is he's teaching piano

384
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:37,541
to some first-year girl.

385
00:17:37,625 --> 00:17:38,833
All: What?!

386
00:17:38,916 --> 00:17:40,708
I demand
you introduce her to me!

387
00:17:40,791 --> 00:17:42,708
How come you knew about this
and I didn't?!

388
00:17:42,791 --> 00:17:45,291
I needed advice on how to deal
with a girl pupil.

389
00:17:45,375 --> 00:17:47,208
Why would I come to you
with that?

390
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:48,666
What did you say,
you little troll!

391
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:49,708
I take it all back,
okay?!

392
00:17:49,791 --> 00:17:51,583
Slipper to the face,
jerk!

393
00:17:51,666 --> 00:17:53,791
Why is everybody
giving me grief about this?

394
00:17:53,875 --> 00:17:55,375
Hiroko forced me to do it.

395
00:17:55,458 --> 00:17:57,583
-It's lipstick!
-Huh? [ Growls ]

396
00:17:57,666 --> 00:17:58,750
Tsubaki: Go on, horn-dog!

397
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,500
Tell us all about this girl!

398
00:18:00,583 --> 00:18:02,291
What have you been
teaching her, huh?!

399
00:18:02,375 --> 00:18:03,333
I never got to date
a first year!

400
00:18:03,416 --> 00:18:05,208
And you really think
you have the time

401
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:06,166
to waste on all of this?

402
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:08,458
Hold on.
I just said that Hiroko --

403
00:18:08,541 --> 00:18:09,625
I don't care.

404
00:18:09,708 --> 00:18:11,750
Whatever lame excuse
you were about to give me,

405
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:12,833
don't bother.
If you have time for some girl,

406
00:18:12,916 --> 00:18:15,250
you'd better
use it on yourself.

407
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:17,000
I work with her a bit
after school,

408
00:18:17,083 --> 00:18:19,250
and then I go home and practice
my own stuff, okay?

409
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:21,791
And I'm telling you
that's not enough!
Uh...

410
00:18:21,875 --> 00:18:23,500
Those hours
aren't coming back ever!

411
00:18:23,583 --> 00:18:25,250
Oh, but you're
the great child prodigy.

412
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:26,583
You can just wing it,
right?!

413
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:28,250
I just told you
that I practice!

414
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:29,583
Whatever you're doing,
double it!

415
00:18:29,666 --> 00:18:31,083
At least then
you're close.

416
00:18:31,166 --> 00:18:33,541
The competitions start
in December, damn it!

417
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:35,416
You're running
on borrowed time as it is!

418
00:18:35,500 --> 00:18:36,500
Before you know it...

419
00:18:36,583 --> 00:18:38,833
[ Gasps ]

420
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:43,375
Wow. [ Chuckles ]

421
00:18:44,916 --> 00:18:47,791
Where did that crazy rant
come from, right?

422
00:18:47,875 --> 00:18:49,875
I'm sorry.

423
00:18:51,583 --> 00:18:52,458
I'm so sorry.

424
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:55,625
[ Playing
"Piano Sonata Number 8" ]

425
00:18:55,708 --> 00:18:58,416
♪♪

426
00:18:58,500 --> 00:18:59,833
[ Chuckles ]
<i>Right about now,</i>

427
00:18:59,916 --> 00:19:03,291
<i>a bit of my lipstick is ruining</i>
<i>your afternoon, Arima.</i>

428
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,541
[ Sighs ]

429
00:19:06,625 --> 00:19:07,625
Satsuki: You must be
having a good day, huh?

430
00:19:07,708 --> 00:19:10,333
Yeah? Why is that?

431
00:19:10,416 --> 00:19:12,375
Your notes sound
like they're skipping along.

432
00:19:12,458 --> 00:19:14,833
Notes can't skip.
They're not alive.

433
00:19:14,916 --> 00:19:17,708
Well, not if you want to get
all technical about it,

434
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:21,708
but, yeah, that's definitely
what they're doing.

435
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:30,708
She's the kind of girl
who already likes my friend.

436
00:19:30,791 --> 00:19:34,375
<i>No way is it gonna work out</i>
<i>for that wimp.</i>

437
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:35,791
<i>He doesn't have a chance.</i>

438
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:38,958
<i>I guess maybe...</i>

439
00:19:39,041 --> 00:19:42,583
<i>that's a way the two of us</i>
<i>are the tiniest bit alike,</i>

440
00:19:42,666 --> 00:19:46,833
<i>chasing the one person</i>
<i>we can never catch up with,</i>

441
00:19:46,916 --> 00:19:49,541
<i>gazing at them</i>
<i>with eyes full of wonder.</i>

442
00:19:49,625 --> 00:19:52,375
<i>For his sake,</i>
<i>I'll do whatever I can</i>

443
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:54,791
<i>to take down Kousei Arima.</i>

444
00:19:57,708 --> 00:19:58,916
<i>A worthy sacrifice...</i>

445
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,333
I'm home!

446
00:20:00,416 --> 00:20:02,500
<i>...for one who</i>
<i>truly deserves it.</i>

447
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:06,833
Hey, you're back.

448
00:20:06,916 --> 00:20:09,166
And kind of early, too.

449
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:12,000
<i>I am the phantom,</i>

450
00:20:12,083 --> 00:20:14,833
<i>the one who lurks</i>
<i>in the opera house.</i>

451
00:20:14,916 --> 00:20:17,041
How was your day,
big brother?

452
00:20:20,875 --> 00:20:22,041
Kaori: Hey.

453
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:23,833
So what'd you bring me?

454
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:26,958
Oh! I forgot them.

455
00:20:27,041 --> 00:20:28,333
Sorry.

456
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:29,958
I shouldn't make you
worry so much.

457
00:20:30,041 --> 00:20:32,583
It's not very nice.
I know.

458
00:20:33,125 --> 00:20:35,083
<i>Not again.</i>

459
00:20:35,166 --> 00:20:37,625
<i>Starting to laugh</i>
<i>out of nowhere.</i>

460
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:40,291
<i>Blowing up</i>
<i>over the tiniest thing.</i>

461
00:20:40,375 --> 00:20:41,708
<i>Sobbing without warning,</i>

462
00:20:41,791 --> 00:20:44,000
<i>then acting so sweet</i>

463
00:20:44,083 --> 00:20:46,708
<i>before giving up</i>
<i>on it all.</i>

464
00:20:47,875 --> 00:20:49,708
<i>That's how</i>
<i>my mom used to be.</i>

465
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,583
<i>Not again.</i>

466
00:20:52,666 --> 00:20:54,458
<i>Please not again.</i>

467
00:20:54,541 --> 00:20:55,666
[ Sighs ]

468
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:56,916
[ Static crackles ]

469
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:57,916
<i>Not you.</i>

470
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,083
[ Static crackles ]

471
00:20:59,166 --> 00:21:00,583
<i>Not like this.</i>

472
00:21:00,666 --> 00:21:02,833
<i>You're just like the book.</i>

473
00:21:02,916 --> 00:21:05,208
<i>"You really are</i>
<i>a strange person.</i>

474
00:21:05,291 --> 00:21:07,041
<i>You come to the hospital</i>
<i>to visit me,</i>

475
00:21:07,125 --> 00:21:09,750
<i>and yet all this time,</i>
<i>you haven't said a word."</i>

476
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:16,291
♪♪

477
00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:17,958
<i>"Want to kill yourself</i>
<i>with me?"</i>

